==Old English==
===Etymology===
From [[ge-|ġe-]] + a Germanic base represented by [[þolian]].  Cognate with Old Saxon [[githuld]] (Dutch [[geduld]]), Old High German [[githult]] (German [[Geduld]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /je'θyld/

===Noun===
'''ġeþyld''' ''n'' or ''f''
# [[patience]], [[resignation]]

